snippet.textDisplay:
Their (h)el(l)evator is destroyed and they’re in a place like the place they shot ‘my pace’ if I’m not right. They’re stuck in a ruined place like in hellevator and voices and Chan is leading them.

SO MY THEORYYY:

Jisung plays a big role in this story, he was the first one to lead them from their reality to the hellevator and they didn’t hesitate follow him through everything because they’re a team. We see them go around the different places in the map together. In district 9, they were sent in a place were they were different (perhaps a dark secret place in Jungle City) and they went against the system, so the people in charge put up clones to confuse them. They experience hardships through themselves (finding themselves) and they solve them. Miroh era, they were fresh and ready to take revenge so they plan to take down the rulers and the people who planned to take them down, but they faced the Side effects of taking down the wrong way because they were changing against what they said they wouldn’t become so they leave the revenge. In double knot they are confident to go anywhere with the key they think is right to solve this all. In astronaut they realize that “oh shi* we left jeongin back” or maybe Jeongin actually knew that the key to go back to reality wasn’t actually true. So, in LAVENTER, they all then realize that the key to go to reality is actually trust. Maybe Jisung didn’t have enough trust in his way or friends in hellevator so he went down the dark hellevator thinking he’d be alone but was with everyone who went through it with him as a team. So as they regain their trust and everything they realize that it was the true key all along. Their confidence opened up the gate again to their reality and normal world. They looked back at everything they once experienced and went through together while leaving this place (or maybe Woojin).
That’s how they stepped out of Clé.

What I think: this idea is so deep in many ways that you can replace it with many other things that could also make sense and relate to this. I hope I got it right >_< what do you think?
